 Set over 2 blocks, both of 44 storeys, Queens Park has 736 well designed units with functional, smart layouts. Units start on the 8th floor and go all the way to the 44th, where the 4 large penthouse suites are located. Queens Park boasts several features that are unusual for a development in this price range, including private lifts and foyers for many of the units, not just the penthouses. Location-wise, Queens Park couldn’t be more convenient for the MRT, as it overlooks the Queenstown Station, and a bridge is being planned to connect the station to the development.
 Project Name: Queens Peak
 Address: Dundee Road
 Type: Condominium
 Site area: approx. 113,194 sqft
 Tenure: 99-year leasehold
 District: 3
 Configuration: 736 units in two blocks of 44-storeys 1 childcare centre

 The station is on the East West Line, 4 and 5 stops from Tanjong Pagar and Raffles Place respectively, meaning residents of Queens Park can be in the CBD within 20 minutes of leaving their homes. Several buses serve the area, with the nearest shopping mall – Dawson Place which has eateries, ATM’s and a NTUC Fairprice, 3 stops away (or a 10 minute walk).

Name: Bijou
Description:
Description
 
1- and 2-bedroom Duplex Units for Lease at Pasir Panjang
 Bijou, a freehold development where sophisticated living transcends into an expression of one's individuality. Experience downtown’s dynamism along the fringes of Singapore’s CBD. This Far East SOHO development perfectly balances urban appeal with classical garden landscapes encircling a rooftop pool and gym.
 
 During National Day Rally 2019, the Singapore Government highlighted on the future transformation plans for Greater Southern Waterfront as part of nation building.
 
 Stretching across 2,000 hectares of land from Pasir Panjang to Gardens by the Bay East, this redevelopment would include a business district, 30-km long scenic waterfront promenade, a green corridor linking Labrador Park to Gardens by the Bay and the development of Pulau Brani into a new tourism attraction – reshaping Greater Southern Waterfront as a new ‘live, work and play’ precinct.
 
 Strategically situated in a tranquil spot directly opposite Pasir Panjang MRT Station, Bijou is in close proximity to key business hubs, retail and recreational venues. Come 2025, Bijou will enjoy added connectivity to the CBD with the completion of the Circle Line loop.
 
 Thrive alongside a diverse and enterprising community of 120 low-rise units; the freehold development is integrated with artisanal retail and F&B options brimming with untapped opportunity. Read More

 This lovely development brings about many simple pleasures of life. Residents get to enjoy the infinity- like pool as a form of leisure or to even perfect the art and skill of the sport. Besides that, there are various plants and trees surrounding the premise, almost appearing to serve as a ‘green hedge of barrier’ against the hustle and bustle of the surrounding townships and city centers nearby. The lush greenery provides a feel of a garden themed residency. It is therapeutic to the nature lover and brings a sense of comfort and peace to all who live in the residence. Besides that, there is a designated barbecue area available for residents who intend to have company over for fellowship and it is also a great way to strengthen bonds besides sharpening certain culinary skills. Apart from that, residents that have been found living in smaller communities tend to cultivate a sense of belonging through the interactions/experiences with other residents. As a result of that, many have been recorded to forge and strengthen friendships over the years. The circumstantial series of events have indirectly opened doors to a new cluster of close- knit communities. Residents have also been cited saying that they also have some form of assurance of security and also a sense of place after settling down in/with small groups of people. Read More

 Sturdee Residences – Unique Selling Points
 
 The location of Sturdee Residences, both in terms of the number of amenities within walking or easy driving distance and its proximity to an MRT line (shortly 2 MRT lines) is by far the biggest plus point in its favour. Several shopping malls, Little India, and a huge array of wining and dining options just a few minutes’ walk from the development are something that projects going for a lot more money cannot match. Facility and looks wise, Sturdee Residences is also has a lot to commend it.
 
 Sturdee Residences – Accessibility
 
 The nearest MRT station to Sturdee Residences is Farrer Park on the North East Line, which is an easy 5 minute walk away. 
 
 Raffles Place is just 9 minutes away for those commuting to the CBD, while City Hall is just 2 stops. Orchard Road is only a little further down the line. 
 
 The forthcoming Bendemeer MRT Station, on the Downtown Line, will be even closer to the development and will offer residents extra options, as well as easing congestion on the existing line.
 
 For those wishing to drive, Sturdee Residences is approximately a 6 minute drive from the CBD, via the CTE, assuming traffic isn’t heavy. There is also a bus stop close to the development, with routes serving many areas of the island.

 Commonwealth Towers
 
 This two towered development benefits from very close proximity to Queenstown MRT Station, on the East West Line, meaning resident of Commonwealth Towers can be in Orchard Road, the CBD or Marina Bay in less than a quarter of an hour and it’s within District 3. Well-designed modern apartment units are a feature of this project from one of the most highly regarded developers in Singapore. The vast majority of the units in Commonwealth Towers are one or two bedrooms, with many of the one bedroom flats having just 441 sqft, making it affordable despite its proximity to the MRT.Commonwealth Towers is developed and built by City Developments Limited (CDL) a Singapore-listed international property and hospitality conglomerate, and one of the biggest landlords on the island. Its extensive global network encompasses more than 400 subsidiaries and associated companies, and owns and manages properties across Asia, Europe the Middle East, North America and New Zealand/Australia. Established in 1963, CDL has won numerous awards both here in Singapore as well as internationally, and has earned itself a reputation for being a socially responsible corporation, championing green and environmentally aware initiatives and projects.
 
 Commonwealth Towers – Unique Selling Points
 
 The number of one and two bedroom units, as well as the relatively small size of them is something that differentiates Commonwealth Towers. The other thing of course is its closeness to the MRT station. Being over the road from a station on the East West Line, is rare, especially this close in to the centre, especially for a new build. The importance that has on the saleability of Commonwealth Towers cannot be overstated. Read More

 Commonwealth Towers
 
 This two towered development benefits from very close proximity to Queenstown MRT Station, on the East West Line, meaning resident of Commonwealth Towers can be in Orchard Road, the CBD or Marina Bay in less than a quarter of an hour and it’s within District 3. Well-designed modern apartment units are a feature of this project from one of the most highly regarded developers in Singapore. The vast majority of the units in Commonwealth Towers are one or two bedrooms, with many of the one bedroom flats having just 441 sqft, making it affordable despite its proximity to the MRT.Commonwealth Towers is developed and built by City Developments Limited (CDL) a Singapore-listed international property and hospitality conglomerate, and one of the biggest landlords on the island. Its extensive global network encompasses more than 400 subsidiaries and associated companies, and owns and manages properties across Asia, Europe the Middle East, North America and New Zealand/Australia. Established in 1963, CDL has won numerous awards both here in Singapore as well as internationally, and has earned itself a reputation for being a socially responsible corporation, championing green and environmentally aware initiatives and projects.
 
 Commonwealth Towers – Unique Selling Points
 
 The number of one and two bedroom units, as well as the relatively small size of them is something that differentiates Commonwealth Towers. The other thing of course is its closeness to the MRT station. Being over the road from a station on the East West Line, is rare, especially this close in to the centre, especially for a new build. The importance that has on the saleability of Commonwealth Towers cannot be overstated. Read More

 North Park Residences
 
 The location is by far and away the biggest draw for North Park Residences, being built as it is on top of Northpoint City – the largest mall in the north of the island. It boasts more than 400 retail and dining options, with Northpoint Link an underground walkway connecting North Park Residences to the Yishun MRT Station home to a further 30. There is also a bus interchange, library, cinema, community club and town plaza on site. North Park Residences itself features 88 facilities of its own, as well as a wide range of unit types.
 
 North Park Residences couldn’t be more conveniently located in terms of transport, retail and indeed dining options, sitting as it does on top of the largest shopping mall in the north of the island. It will be connected to Yishun MRT Station on the North South Line via Northpoint Link, an underground walkway that itself will be home to 30 retail outlets. From there Orchard Road is 9 stops, with the CBD a further 3 away, meaning commuters can comfortably be door to door in under half an hour. Description:
Description
 
Mins Walk to Somerset MRT & 313 Orchard Central!
 Lloyd Sixty Five is situated between River Valley and Orchard Road, two of the most sought after locations on the island, Lloyd Sixty Five is ideally placed. Just far enough off Killiney, so as not to suffer traffic noise, the development is a 5-minute walk or less from Somerset MRT, the shopping on Orchard Road, the restaurants on Killiney Road as well as a 24-hour supermarket. Lloyd Sixty Five itself is a smart, high-end residential development that offers its residents high ceilinged units featuring large balconies and an array of facilities. A commute into the CBD from Lloyd Sixty Five is achievable in 15 minutes.TG Development is a multi-award winning developer that specializes in luxury urban housing. Since 1987, it has been responsible for many influential projects from terrace houses, semi-detached homes, good class bungalows to apartments and condominiums.
 
 Set just off the lively Killiney Road, Lloyd Sixty Five is a high quality – posh – residential development. Its 76 units are all in one, 10 storey tower, and the first thing you notice is the high ceilings in all units – 5.9 to 6.0 meters. The units are also characterized by high quality imported flooring and large, expansive balconies, that seamlessly meld into the living quarters. Facilities include a swimming pool
 
 The main advantage of Lloyd Sixty Five is that there is practically everything you would need in very easy walking distance. A 24-hour NTUC Fairprice is 2 minutes away, along with ATM’s. Killiney Road is packed with eateries, bars, and bakeries, and Orchard Road is only a couple of minutes further along. The nearest MRT to Lloyd Sixty Five is Somerset on the North-South Line. From there it is just 2 stops to City Hall, and 3 to Raffles Place. Dhoby Ghaut is 1 stop from Somerset from where you can change to the Circle and North East Lines.

 - 1 BR Apartment With Balcony
 - Partial Furnished. 
 - Available Immediately.

 VAacant

 At a staggering 250 metres, Altez brings a new perspective to the term “high-life”. The 62-storey development offers panoramic views of the sea and the city, and full condominium facilities. Just two minutes’ walk from Tanjong Pagar MRT Station, residents enjoy excellent access to the Central Business District and the Marina Coastal Expressway (MCE).
 URA Draft Master Plan 2019 highlighted the Downtown transformation plan and The Greater Southern Waterfront development plan. Strategically located at downtown Tanjong Pagar, Altez is well-positioned to benefit from the enlivening enhancements of both zones.
 The Downtown transformation plan focuses on the various needs of modern lifestyles, increasing conveniences and connectivity to create a vibrant place for the modern working professional to live and work in. 
 The Greater Southern Waterfront development plan spans across 2,000 hectares from Gardens by the Bay East to Pasir Panjang. It promises an attractive waterfront promenade where various places of interests, like the historic Tanjong Pagar Railway, would be connected. 
 The development is also directly linked to Icon Village, a destination mall designed to create a cosmopolitan lifestyle, and a short walk away from 100 AM retail mall. Read More

 Martin Place Residences offers its residences a wide range of facilities. They include swimming pool, children’s pool, clubhouse with function room, gymnasium,

 yoga corner, sky lounge, and even a water garden. 
 
 
 Martin Place Residences is just minutes away from Orchard Road shopping belt where a whole bunch of amenities awaits you. 
 Also just minutes away from killiney road, residents can enjoy the wide range of trendy bistros and bars there. 
 Some of them include The Book Cafe, Brown Sugar Cafe Bistro, and Yoyogi Restaurant.

 Scotts Square is a freehold apartment development located at 6-8 Scotts Road, Singapore 228209, in District 09, minutes walk from Orchard MRT Station. Completed in 2010, it has a total of 43 storeys and comprises of 338 units. The Orchard Road shopping district and Singapore Botanic Gardens are just some of the many attractions located nearby. 
 
 Condo Facilities at Scotts Square 
 
 Facilities at Scotts Square include swimming pool, sky pool, fitness room, recreation room, reading room, meeting room, and drawing room.
 
 Condo Amenities near Scotts Square 
 
 Scotts Square is located close to several prestigious local and international schools, such as Raffles Girls’ School and Chatsworth International School. Numerous restaurants and eateries are located along the stretch of Scotts Road and are within walking distance. 
 
 With its proximity to Orchard Road shopping belt, residents have a myriad of amenities available at several one-stop shopping destinations, such as Ion Orchard, Takashimaya, The Paragon, and Wisma Atria. Recreational facilities nearby include esteemed clubs such as American Club and Tanglin Club. In addition, Mount Elizabeth Hospital is a short walk away.

It is three, Residential towers with 429 units. It has 117 1 bedroom units of 480-580 square feet, 234 2 bedroom units of 650-900 square feet, and 78 3bedroom units of 1,080-1,350 square feet.
 
 Location
 
 The Park Place Residences @PLQ can be accessed via the Nicoll Highway and PIE. The Paya Lebar MRT station connects the east to the west line with a circle line as an interchange.It is a single stop to Eunos MRT station and buses are available from here and go to Bedok, Marine Parade and other parts of Geylang area.
 
 Facilities

 The Park Place Residences @PLQ residents will enjoy Wi-Fi being offered around the Paya Lebar Quarter which will enable office occupants to be able to work outdoors as well.  Set over 2 blocks, both of 44 stories, Queens Park has 736 well-designed units with functional, smart layouts. Units start on the 8th floor and go all the way to the 44th, where the 4 large penthouse suites are located. Queens Park boasts several features that are unusual for development in this price range, including private lifts and foyers for many of the units, not just the penthouses. Location-wise, Queens Park couldn’t be more convenient for the MRT, as it overlooks the Queenstown Station, and a bridge is being planned to connect the station to the development.
 Project Name: Queens Peak
 Address: Dundee Road
 Type: Condominium
 Site area: approx. 113,194 sqft
 Tenure: 99-year leasehold

 The station is on the East West Line, 4 and 5 stops from Tanjong Pagar and Raffles Place respectively, meaning residents of Queens Park can be in the CBD within 20 minutes of leaving their homes. Several buses serve the area, with the nearest shopping mall – Dawson Place which has eateries, ATM’s and a NTUC Fairprice, 3 stops away (or a 10 minute walk).

 The Shore Residences have full facilities, which includes swimming pool, Jacuzzi, sauna, BBQ pits, gym, tennis courts, badminton court, and playground.
 
 Condo Amenities near The Shore Residences
 
 Numerous feeder bus services are available near The Shore Residences. Several good schools are in the vicinity, including Tanjong Katong Secondary School, Chung Cheng High School, and Victoria Junior College.
 
 The Shore Residences is also within walking distance to the stretch of restaurants located at East Coast Road and Marine Parade Road. Residents can head down to the nearby Parkway Parade or surrounding shopping malls for a host of amenities, such as supermarkets, restaurants and eating establishments, banks, boutique shops, and more. In addition, the Parkland Golf Driving Range is just a short drive away.

Name: Sophia Hills
Description:
Description
 
Short Walk to MRT & Move In Immediate
 Sophia Hills, is a very well-designed development built in a historic residential enclave in the heart of Singapore. In terms of its positions, Sophia Hills is ideal, with a Cineplex, shopping malls, wide choice of restaurants and 3 MRT lines (Circle, North East and North South) all within very easy walking distance. Commuters will be able to get into the CBD within 20 minutes or less and it’s within District 9.
 
 Accessibility and connectivity are the two key words when it comes to Sophia Hills, with many of the island’s greatest attractions within walking distance, as well as a very wide variety of retail, entertainment and dining options. Its proximity to 3 MRT lines, plus the CBD also means it is very handy for commuters. The development itself is very impressive as well however, as is its immediate environment sat up on a quiet residential and historic enclave, something that the design of Sophia Hills makes the most of.
 
 Sophia Hills is very centrally and therefore conveniently located. Plaza Singapura is just over 5 minutes’ walk away with over 300 retail outlets including a Cold Storage, and the other malls along Orchard Road an easy walk or short bus ride away. The Cathay Cineplex is 300 yards from the development, while Little India is a 10 minute walk. The nearest MRT to Sophia Hills is Dhoby Ghaut on the Circle, North East and North South Lines, giving quick and easy access to all areas of the island. Raffles Place is two stops away, Clarke Quay just one.

 Amenities near Sims Urban Oasis 
 Sims Urban Oasis is also in the midst of many existing and future landmark projects. These include the Singapore Sports Hub to the South, the upcoming Paya Lebar Sub-Regional Centre to the East, the new Kallang Riverside waterfront district to the West, and the future Bidadari Estate to the North. 
 
 Sims Urban Oasis is poised to rejuvenate a charming and accessible locale of Singapore. With well-designed homes and quality amenities, the 2.4 hectare development will seed a positive transformation of Sims Drive. Upon completion, a total of 1,024 units will cater various apartment types for multi-generation living, families, young couples, singles and their diverse lifestyles.

 Valley Park is a 999-years leasehold development located at 473 – 483 River Valley Road, Singapore 248358, in District 10, minutes walk to Tiong Bahru MRT Station. Completed in 1997, it comprises 728 units. Valley Park is close to Fort Canning Park and Great World City. 
 
 Condo Facilities at Valley Park 
 
 Facilities at Valley Park include 24 hours security, swimming pool, BBQ pits, gym, tennis and squash courts, sauna, clubhouse, mini-mart, and playground. 
 
 Condo Amenities near Valley Park 
 
 Several feeder bus services are available near Valley Park. Schools are mostly a short drive away, including Crescent Girls’ School, Overseas Family School, and ISS International School. 
 
 Valley Park is also within walking distance to the stretch of restaurants located at River Valley Road. Residents can head down to the nearby Great World City mall for amenities such as supermarkets, restaurants and eating establishments, banks, cinema, and boutique shops. There is also a free shuttle service from Great World City to Orchard Road. In addition, it is just a short drive to Camden Medical Centre. 
 
 For vehicle owners, driving from Valley Park to either the business hub or the bustling Orchard Road shopping district takes less than 10 minutes, via Havelock Road and Paterson Road respectively.

 One Shenton, located in the heart of Marina Bay features 341 ultra-luxurious developments in a much sought after area. From its location near the equidistant between the bay and the Singapore River, One Shenton is in easy reach of the vibrant night life of Clarke and Boat Quays, as well as the business hub of the nation. Impressive transport links means residents of One Shenton can quickly and easily access all parts of the island by both MRT and car. The modern, exquisitely designed homes, available in 1 bedroom up to 4 bedroom units, as well as sky suites and villas, all feature state of the art facilities, fixtures and fittings.One Shenton is developed and built by City Developments Limited (CDL) a Singapore-listed international property and hospitality conglomerate, and one of the biggest landlords on the island. Its extensive global network encompasses more than 400 subsidiaries and associated companies, and owns and manages properties across Asia, Europe the Middle East, North America and New Zealand/Australia. Established in 1963, CDL has won numerous awards both here in Singapore as well as internationally, and has earned itself a reputation for being a socially responsible corporation, championing green and environmentally aware initiatives and projects
 
 One Shenton – Unique Selling Points
 One Shenton stands out, and not just because of its stunning asymmetrical design or golden tones. The development is designed by the world famous architect Carlos Ott, and will quickly become an iconic addition to the already world famous Singapore skyline. It isn’t just something to be enjoyed from without though, One Shenton sets the bar very high when it comes to luxury. Every one of its 341 units are designed to exacting modern standards, and offer an oasis of calm in the often hectic city. Read More

Description:

Quiet facing 1 beroom full facilities near braddell mrt!
 1 bedder partial furnished!
 
 contact Lucas Chen 9105....91051360 for viewing!
 
 Gem Residences – Unique Selling Points
 
 While the location may be uninspiring, Gem Residences in itself is a unique development, and one that makes light of its immediate surroundings. Somewhere in the grey area between a hotel and a condominium, Gem Residences offers an array of features and services that would be impressive in an extremely high end development. These include the ability for residents to order from food menus from their concierge that are then delivered to their homes. The concierge also offers a service for grocery shopping. Gem Residences also provides housekeeping, pet pools and fitness classes. Fully trained medical staff are also on site.
 
 Gem Residences – Accessibility
 
 Gem Residences is close to a wide variety of local eateries, and there are also places for grocery shopping. The concierge services available onsite however may well make those choices redundant. With regards to the MRT, Gem Residences is not quite as convenient, located where it is in between Braddell and Toa Payoh stations. Neither are particularly close, Braddell is slightly nearer to the development but it is still a 15 to 20 minute walk. Once on the train things improve. They are both on the North South Line, with Newton two stops away, and Orchard and City hall a few further on.

 Toa Payoh, literally means "big swamp" in Hokkien dialect, which references the large swampy area that the town used to be. As one of the oldest residential estates and its central location in Singapore, Toa Payoh is a vibrant town bustling with activities. The Toa Payoh New Town was built in 1968 as HDB's second satellite town in regards to urban planning principles of the time.
 
 The self-contained housing estate has a town centre acting as a focal point of the retail and entertainment at the convenience of the residents. Since 2002, HDB's headquarters have relocated to HDB Hub located in Toa Payoh Central. With a total of 12 subzones, Toa Payoh is home to approximately 109,000 HDB residents and 36,616 flats. Description:
Description
 
Modern 1 Bedder Condo For Rent
 ***Renovated 1 Bedder For Rent***
 
 - 1Br1B, 484sqf
 - High floor
 - Corner unit
 - Bright and well maintained
 - Unblocked view
 - 10 mins drive to city
 
 Principal Garden is located at Prince Charles Crescent in District 3, and has a total of 663 units.
 
 Principal Garden is strategically situated in a mature and tranquil neighborhood which is well-connected to the public transportation at the same time. Surrounded by Good Class bungalows, this private estate is truly an exclusive habitat for families and singles alike.
 
 - Developed by prominent developer – UOL
 
 - Within 10 minutes’ drive to Orchard Road, CBD, Marina Bay and Southern Waterfront City.
 
 - Potential tenants and buyers from One-North, Mapletree Business Park, NUS, NUH and business centres in Tiong Bahru.
 
 estled in a quiet enclave along the recreational waterway of Alexandra Canal, on the fringe of the embassy district, Principal Garden reflects a new daring in residential design thinking that purposefully seeks to maximise unbuilt space amid the density of urban Singapore.
 Discover the rare luxury of a home where an overwhelming abundance of outdoor space immerses you in the pleasures of garden living. And where the sense of space is multiplied by uninhibited views that stretch from the low-rise surroundings all the way to the CBD and Orchard Road.
 
 Comprising four 24-storey towers, home to 663 one- to five-bedroom apartments, Principal Garden is delightfully private yet incredibly well connected. Appreciate the convenience of residing just minutes from Redhill MRT, a short drive to the CTE and AYE, within walking distance of supermarkets, wet markets, hawker centres and schools, and a stone’s throw from Singapore’s core commercial and financial districts.
 
 Revel in the variety of life in the surrounding neighbourhoods, from Tanglin and Orchard Road to Tiong Bahru, and along the riverside from Alexandra Canal to Robertson Quay. Read More

Description:
Description
 
Double volume super high ceiling 1 bedroom! Panoramic views!
 The Tribeca by the Waterfront is a condominium project which is located in Kim Seng Road, 239497, Orchard / Holland (D09-10) District 9. It was completed in 2010, it comprises of 30 storeys and 175 units. Tribeca By the Waterfront offers a wide range of facilities at your disposal. These include swimming pool, lap pool, wading pool, family pool, reflecting pools, function room, gymnasium, meeting room, granite decks, timber decks, pool pavilion, ponds, pocket courts, sunken gardens, playgrounds, barbeque pavilions, sculpture, tennis courts, and car park. 24 units are available for buying purpose and 7 for rental purpose. The tenure of this project is freehold property.
 
 City Developments Limited are the developers of this project. Skilled workers of Singapore are responsible for building this Condominium projects numerous terraced house, housing projects and condominiums. The Project promises a luxurious high life, on a luxurious high-rise apartment.
 
 Tribeca by the Waterfront - Unique Selling Points
 
 The main objective of Tribeca by the Waterfront is to provide a friendly and safe environment to the residents. It is a family oriented project which has many amenities around it. The architect of the building is very unique with strong construction. There are artificial plants with lightning around to enhance the beauty of the place. All the facilities are available at an affordable price. The developer has put in a lot of effort to give it a sense of luxury lifestyle in the apartment. One must not miss this opportunity to invest in this project. Strict security system is ensured to protect families with kids.
 
 Tribeca by the Waterfront - Accessibilities
 
 Tribeca by the Waterfront is a freehold condominium located at Kim Seng Road in District D09. Tribeca by The Waterfront is close to Tiong Bahru MRT EW17. TE16 Havelock MRT Station, TE15 Great World MRT Station and DE20 Fort Canning MRT Station are the nearest to the condomonium. Read More

 Queens Peak – Unique Selling Points
 
 Accessibility is a big draw for Queens Park, with its close proximity to Queenstown MRT Station on the East West Line. Three stops takes you to Outram Park on the North East Line, while raffles Place is another two stops along on the East West. With regards to the project itself, Queens P ark has 736 units that range from 425 sqft one bedroom flats up to 4 and 5 bedroom units, as well as 4 extremely large penthouses, measuring an impressive 4,778 sqft. All are functionally yet stylishly designed and laid out, with many having their own private lifts and foyers, something almost unheard of for non-luxury developments
 
 Queens Peak – Accessibility
 
 Queens Park actually overlooks Queenstown MRT station, and there are plans to connect the two with a covered bridge. The station is on the East West Line, 4 and 5 stops from Tanjong Pagar and Raffles Place respectively, meaning residents of Queens Park can be in the CBD within 20 minutes of leaving their homes. Several buses serve the area, with the nearest shopping mall – Dawson Place which has eateries, ATM’s and a NTUC Fairprice, 3 stops away (or a 10 minute walk).

 This mixed development site in the much sought after Marina Bay area, features 1,042 high end luxury residential units as well as several internationally renowned retail and dining outlets. What makes Marina One Residences stand out however, is its very own biodiversity garden – The Green Heart, which gives the whole development a feeling of calm and tranquillity despite being located right in the centre of one of the busiest cities in the world. Marina One Residences is also convenient for 4 MRT lines, while 4 nearby expressways give access to all parts of the island.Marina One Residences is owned and developed by M + S Pte Ltd, a joint venture between Malaysia’s Khazanah Nasional Berhad and Singapore investment company, Temasek Holdings Pte. Ltd that was set up in 2011 purely to build Marina One Residences and Duo. 
 
 Marina One Residencies - Unique Selling Points
 
 Despite its location in a concrete and steel jungle, Marina One Residences features its very own tropical paradise – “The Green Heart”. This 65,000 sqft biodiversity garden features its own 13.2 metre high waterfall, which acts not just as a calming and defining presence for the development but also as the main thoroughfare for the residents.Marina One Residences also features 140,000 sqft of retail, lifestyle and F&B space. High profile brands are already in situ, including a Virgin Active, Cold Storage, Japanese restaurant Teppei Syokudo, and a Koufu operated foodcourt featuring its novel Cookhouse concept. Read More

Description
 
City Square Residence
 City Square Residences is a freehold development located at 2-14 Kitchener Link, near Serangoon Road, in District 08. Completed in 2009 and scaling 30 storeys, this 910-unit development has picture-perfect views of the city. 
 
 City Square Residences offers a myriad of facilities, which includes a swimming pool, lap pool, covered car park, 24 hours security, BBQ pits, gym, fitness station, tennis courts, putting green, steam bath, Jacuzzi, clubhouse, function room, games room, karaoke room, a playground and even a bowling alley. 
 
 Located in prime District 08, many amenities surround City Square. Several bus services are available in the vicinity and it is a short walk from Farrer Park MRT station. Schools and restaurants are located nearby. 
 
 Shopping centres nearby include Mustafa Centre and the upcoming City Square Mall. Attractions such as Little India and The Istana are a stone’s throw away and Raffles Hospital is within reasonable driving distance. 
 
 For vehicle owners, travelling to the CBD and the vibrant Orchard Road shopping belt takes a mere 10 minutes, via Victoria Street and Scotts Road respectively. 
 
 City Square Residences is situated in an excellent location a short stroll away from Farrer Park station, and getting by car to the Central Business District is a swift journey by the Central Expressway. Choice schools nearby are easily accessible, the popular 24-hour Mustafa is a short walk away, and when construction is completed a grand hypermarket would be right next door to City Square residents. In addition, the number of other shops, stores, and food centres nearby ensure variety and the opportunity to try something new everyday is possible. Read More

Name: Gem Residences
Description:
Description
 
Very High floor 1 bedroom for rent
 Gem Residences 1 bedroom for rent. Be the 1st to stay in this beautiful condominium. 
 
 
 Gem Residences
 
 Gem Residences is a residential development in District 12’s Toa Payoh. It is a 15 to 20 minutes’ walk to its nearest MRT station – Braddell on the North South Line, though the development is surrounded by a number of eateries. A number of arterial roads in the vicinity mean getting away by car is a fairly easy task. Gem Residences 578 units are made up of a good split of different configurations, and include dual key and triple key options. By far the biggest thing going for Gem Residences however is the hotel type concept that it has. The concierge will arrange food orders from a provided menu – delivered to your door, the same service is also available for groceries. Fully trained medical staff are on site, and the development also provides such activities as fitness classes while there is a pet pool for dogs.Gem Residences is the first residential development by Venture capitalists Evia Capital Partners Pte Ltd. founded in 2004.
 
 Gem Residences – Unique Selling Points
 
 While the location may be uninspiring, Gem Residences in itself is a unique development, and one that makes light of its immediate surroundings. Somewhere in the grey area between a hotel and a condominium, Gem Residences offers an array of features and services that would be impressive in an extremely high end development. These include the ability for residents to order from food menus from their concierge that are then delivered to their homes. The concierge also offers a service for grocery shopping. Gem Residences also provides housekeeping, pet pools and fitness classes. Fully trained medical staff are also on site. Read More
